sql:
SELECT SUM(trips) AS total_trips
FROM mobility
WHERE county_id = 0;

SELECT trips, distance_traveled
FROM mobility
WHERE county_id = 1 AND date = '2020-07-06';

external_knowledge:
Latest version of the data refers to the version with the highest version number; 
 The average population density is the sum of population densities divided by the number of versions of the data for each county; 
 Total number of trips refers to the sum of all trips made in each county.

sql:
SELECT SUM(trips) AS total_trips, SUM(distance_traveled) AS total_distance
FROM mobility
WHERE date = '2020-07-06';
